🔴 **Design Issue** — `AzureClouds` enum naming violates `Known*` convention

Every other extensible enum in this package uses the `Known*` prefix (e.g., `KnownActionType`, `KnownProvisioningState`, `KnownRefillPolicy`). The new `AzureClouds` enum breaks that pattern.

**Expected shape:**
```ts
// `@public`
export enum KnownAzureSupportedClouds {
    AzureChinaCloud = "AZURE_CHINA_CLOUD",
    AzurePublicCloud = "AZURE_PUBLIC_CLOUD",
    AzureUsGovernment = "AZURE_US_GOVERNMENT"
}

// `@public`
export type AzureSupportedClouds = string;
```

**Fix:** Rename `AzureClouds` → `KnownAzureSupportedClouds` (or `KnownAzureClouds`) and update all references. Report in the [generation tool repository](https://github.com/Azure/autorest.typescript/issues).
